00:45:14.110 --> 00:45:20.370
My research is on the American
expedition to Siberia between 1918

00:45:20.370 --> 00:45:28.500 position:56%
and 1920 when the Entente intervened
into the Russian Civil War.

00:45:28.500 --> 00:45:31.930
This is another map, I am
following the previous presenters.

00:45:31.930 --> 00:45:38.300
It's not easy to count exactly
how many countries participated,

00:45:38.300 --> 00:45:43.130
but according to Winston
Churchill totaled 14 countries,

00:45:43.130 --> 00:45:45.850
including the United States.

00:45:45.850 --> 00:45:52.870
This is a military map, so the
blue color shows the [inaudible].

00:45:52.870 --> 00:46:05.070 position:56%
And the red color shows where allied
and [inaudible] forces were located.

00:46:05.070 --> 00:46:11.760
The allies conducted [inaudible]
and counterinsurgency operations

00:46:11.760 --> 00:46:13.970
against the Bolshevik Reds.

00:46:13.970 --> 00:46:18.170
Since this controversial
[inaudible] is inseparably tied

00:46:18.170 --> 00:46:21.400
to the Russian revolution
and the Civil War in Russia,

00:46:21.400 --> 00:46:26.440
we have incalculable number
of publications on this topic.

00:46:26.440 --> 00:46:31.130
Naturally the very fact of the
U.S. troops haven't been operated

00:46:31.130 --> 00:46:34.170
in Russia, the fact of
[inaudible] interference

00:46:34.170 --> 00:46:40.230
in the Russian Civil War
creates ample opportunities

00:46:40.230 --> 00:46:44.400
for it being utilized
as a convenient tool

00:46:44.400 --> 00:46:48.280
for anti-American propaganda
campaigns.

00:46:48.280 --> 00:46:51.370
Unsurprisingly, the
narratives that have been formed

00:46:51.370 --> 00:46:56.340
for 100 years mirrored all
the abrupt shifts in Soviet

00:46:56.340 --> 00:46:58.010
and Russian American relations.

00:46:58.010 --> 00:47:03.990
And, of course, due to the recent
rise of [inaudible] Americanism

00:47:03.990 --> 00:47:06.950
in Russian, now these
narratives are often used

00:47:06.950 --> 00:47:09.010
by the Russian propagandists.

00:47:09.010 --> 00:47:13.710
The main goal of my research is
not the study of these events,

00:47:13.710 --> 00:47:18.900
not the study of these events,
but investigation of historical

00:47:18.900 --> 00:47:23.120
and political contexts in which
the main interpretation is both

00:47:23.120 --> 00:47:27.610 position:56%
in Russian and English where
written, as well as how ideological,

00:47:27.610 --> 00:47:31.720 position:56%
political, and social
affiliations of the numerous writers

00:47:31.720 --> 00:47:38.190
of these events shape the narrative
-- the narratives they produced.

00:47:38.190 --> 00:47:43.440 position:56%
While doing my research I identified
the two dominating Russian language

00:47:43.440 --> 00:47:47.340
narratives, which can be
conventionally named the red

00:47:47.340 --> 00:47:48.770
and the white.

00:47:48.770 --> 00:47:51.720
The red, or the Soviet
communist party narrative,

00:47:51.720 --> 00:47:54.020
consists of two interpretations.

00:47:54.020 --> 00:47:57.650
One is the [inaudible]
illusion created by the group

00:47:57.650 --> 00:48:01.560
of Marxist historians
led by Pokrovsky,

00:48:01.560 --> 00:48:06.630
who in 1919 himself actively
participated in the negotiations

00:48:06.630 --> 00:48:11.620
on signing separate peace treaty
between Russia and Germany.

00:48:11.620 --> 00:48:17.860
Being vehemently anti-British,
anti-French, and anti-Japanese,

00:48:17.860 --> 00:48:21.660
this group asserted that the United
States has not recognized the

00:48:21.660 --> 00:48:25.500
intervention and American
participation

00:48:25.500 --> 00:48:29.610
in the real fighting was
actually very limited.

00:48:29.610 --> 00:48:32.970
Even though they harshly
criticized President Wilson

00:48:32.970 --> 00:48:35.500
for his [inaudible] imperialistic

00:48:35.500 --> 00:48:38.740
and now colonial foreign
policy disguised

00:48:38.740 --> 00:48:43.160
under democratic [inaudible],

00:48:43.160 --> 00:48:49.490
I would say that this
narrative was rather favorable.

00:48:49.490 --> 00:48:54.290
In the 1930's this
narrative was reconsidered due

00:48:54.290 --> 00:48:57.680
to internal political struggle
in the Soviet leadership

00:48:57.680 --> 00:49:01.060
and the rapidly changing
international situation

00:49:01.060 --> 00:49:04.230
on the eve of the World War II.

00:49:04.230 --> 00:49:08.700
Following the deterioration of
Soviet Japanese relations that led

00:49:08.700 --> 00:49:12.350
to the civil [inaudible] wars,
the Soviet historians claimed

00:49:12.350 --> 00:49:15.930
that they recognize that
the most active participant

00:49:15.930 --> 00:49:19.620
of the [inaudible] intervention
has been imperial Japan

00:49:19.620 --> 00:49:26.230
and Trotsky has been accused of
being a German and Japanese spy.

00:49:26.230 --> 00:49:30.040
The beginning of the Cold War;
however, resulted in creation

00:49:30.040 --> 00:49:34.510
of the narrative where America was
viewed as the organizer and sponsor

00:49:34.510 --> 00:49:37.360
of the Entente intervention.

00:49:37.360 --> 00:49:40.850
This narrative dominated
official Soviet historiography

00:49:40.850 --> 00:49:44.450
up to the 1990's when
it was replaced

00:49:44.450 --> 00:49:47.870
by the anti-communist
white narrative.

00:49:47.870 --> 00:49:53.410
It is worth mentioning that
nowadays Russia is undergoing kind

00:49:53.410 --> 00:49:57.650
of white renaissance,
everything somehow related

00:49:57.650 --> 00:50:01.960
to the white movement
[inaudible] values, songs,

00:50:01.960 --> 00:50:05.830
literature are extremely
popular in Russia.

00:50:05.830 --> 00:50:10.520
There are many drama films and
[inaudible] produced recently

00:50:10.520 --> 00:50:13.850
that unlike the abandoned
Soviet narrative [inaudible]

00:50:13.850 --> 00:50:16.430
prerevolutionary Russia

00:50:16.430 --> 00:50:20.320
and anti-Bolshevik white
movement favorably.

00:50:20.320 --> 00:50:26.770
And the reds [inaudible] as radical
fanatics whose main purpose was

00:50:26.770 --> 00:50:30.710
destruction of Russia
and its peoples.

00:50:30.710 --> 00:50:33.470
I think that the surprising
popularity

00:50:33.470 --> 00:50:36.420
of the defeated whites
can be partially explained

00:50:36.420 --> 00:50:39.630
by the communist party
efforts to erase the memory

00:50:39.630 --> 00:50:42.910
of the white movement
from Russia's history.

00:50:42.910 --> 00:50:47.170
However, the 70 years of the
red narrative domination proved

00:50:47.170 --> 00:50:50.010
to be counterproductive.

00:50:50.010 --> 00:50:55.380 position:56%
The white interpretations of the
American intervention can be divided

00:50:55.380 --> 00:51:00.120 position:56%
into two sub narratives, the one
created by the supporters of Russian

00:51:00.120 --> 00:51:03.570
and -- of Russian anti-Bolshevik
socialist parties

00:51:03.570 --> 00:51:07.520
and the one created by
the Russian rightists.

00:51:07.520 --> 00:51:12.360
The letter included not only
far right loyalists advocating

00:51:12.360 --> 00:51:17.200
restoration of [inaudible] dynasty,
but also [inaudible] conservatives

00:51:17.200 --> 00:51:21.120
and nationalists who
oppose the socialists.

00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:22.930
One would think that the whites,

00:51:22.930 --> 00:51:26.510
who refused to recognize the
Bolshevik treaty with Germany

00:51:26.510 --> 00:51:30.320
and continue to fight
on the American side,

00:51:30.320 --> 00:51:33.730
